# C++ Learning Roadmap - Basic to Advanced

## üå± Level 1: Fundamentals

### 1. Introduction & Setup
- Setting up C++ compiler (GCC, Clang, MSVC)
- IDE setup (VS Code, CLion, Visual Studio)
- Writing first program (Hello World)
- Compilation process
- Header files and source files

### 2. Basic Syntax
- Comments (single-line, multi-line)
- Variables and data types
- Constants and literals
- Type casting and type conversion
- Input/Output (cin, cout)
- Escape sequences

### 3. Data Types
- Primitive types (int, float, double, char, bool)
- Type modifiers (signed, unsigned, short, long)
- Size of data types
- Auto keyword
- Type aliases (typedef, using)

### 4. Operators
- **Arithmetic operators** (+, -, *, /, %, ++, --)
- **Relational operators** (==, !=, <, >, <=, >=)
- **Logical operators** (&&, ||, !)
- **Bitwise operators** (&, |, ^, ~, <<, >>)
- **Assignment operators** (=, +=, -=, *=, /=, etc.)
- **Ternary operator** (?:)
- **Comma operator**
- **sizeof operator**
- Operator precedence and associativity

### 5. Control Flow
- If-else statements
- Switch-case statements
- Loops (for, while, do-while)
- Break and continue
- Goto statement (and why to avoid it)
- Nested loops and statements

## üåø Level 2: Intermediate Basics

### 6. Functions
- Function declaration and definition
- Function parameters and return types
- Pass by value vs pass by reference
- Default arguments
- Function overloading
- Inline functions
- Recursion
- Function pointers

### 7. Arrays
- One-dimensional arrays
- Multi-dimensional arrays
- Array initialization
- Passing arrays to functions
- Array of pointers
- Character arrays and strings

### 8. Pointers
- Pointer basics and syntax
- Pointer arithmetic
- Null pointers
- Void pointers
- Pointer to pointer (double pointers)
- Pointers and arrays
- Pointers and functions
- Dynamic memory allocation (new, delete)
- Memory leaks and dangling pointers

### 9. References
- Reference variables
- Reference vs pointers
- Const references
- Reference as function parameters
- Reference as return type

### 10. Strings
- C-style strings
- std::string class
- String operations and methods
- String manipulation
- String streams (stringstream)

## üå≥ Level 3: Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)

### 11. Classes and Objects
- Class definition and syntax
- Access specifiers (public, private, protected)
- Member variables and methods
- Constructors (default, parameterized, copy)
- Destructors
- this pointer
- Static members
- Friend functions and classes
- Const member functions

### 12. Encapsulation
- Data hiding
- Getters and setters
- Access control

### 13. Inheritance
- Single inheritance
- Multiple inheritance
- Multilevel inheritance
- Hierarchical inheritance
- Hybrid inheritance
- Constructor and destructor in inheritance
- Access control in inheritance
- Virtual base classes
- Diamond problem

### 14. Polymorphism
- Function overloading (compile-time)
- Operator overloading
- Virtual functions (runtime polymorphism)
- Pure virtual functions
- Abstract classes
- Virtual destructors
- Early binding vs late binding
- Virtual function table (vtable)

### 15. Abstraction
- Abstract classes
- Interfaces
- Pure virtual functions

## üå≤ Level 4: Advanced Features

### 16. Templates
- Function templates
- Class templates
- Template specialization
- Template parameters
- Variadic templates
- SFINAE (Substitution Failure Is Not An Error)
- Template metaprogramming basics

### 17. Standard Template Library (STL)
- **Containers**:
  - Vector
  - List
  - Deque
  - Stack
  - Queue
  - Priority Queue
  - Set and Multiset
  - Map and Multimap
  - Unordered Set/Map
  - Array
- **Iterators**:
  - Iterator types
  - Iterator operations
  - Const iterators
  - Reverse iterators
- **Algorithms**:
  - Sorting (sort, stable_sort)
  - Searching (find, binary_search)
  - Modifying (copy, fill, transform)
  - Numeric (accumulate, inner_product)
  - Min/Max operations
- **Functors** (Function objects)
- **Lambda expressions**

### 18. Exception Handling
- Try-catch blocks
- Throw statement
- Standard exceptions
- Custom exceptions
- Exception specifications
- RAII (Resource Acquisition Is Initialization)
- noexcept specifier

### 19. File Handling
- File streams (ifstream, ofstream, fstream)
- Reading and writing files
- Binary file operations
- File modes
- File pointers and seeking
- Error handling in file operations

### 20. Namespaces
- Creating namespaces
- Using directive
- Using declaration
- Nested namespaces
- Anonymous namespaces
- Namespace aliasing

## üèîÔ∏è Level 5: Modern C++ (C++11/14/17/20/23)

### 21. Smart Pointers
- unique_ptr
- shared_ptr
- weak_ptr
- Custom deleters
- make_unique and make_shared

### 22. Move Semantics
- Rvalue references
- Move constructors
- Move assignment operators
- std::move
- Perfect forwarding
- Universal references

### 23. Modern Features
- Auto keyword (type inference)
- Range-based for loops
- nullptr
- constexpr
- static_assert
- Uniform initialization
- Initializer lists
- Structured bindings (C++17)
- if/switch with initializer (C++17)

### 24. Lambda Expressions
- Lambda syntax
- Capture clauses
- Mutable lambdas
- Generic lambdas
- Lambda and algorithms

### 25. Multithreading
- std::thread
- Mutexes and locks
- Condition variables
- Atomic operations
- Future and promise
- async and launch policies
- Thread pools
- Race conditions and deadlocks

### 26. Type Traits and Metaprogramming
- Type traits
- SFINAE techniques
- Concepts (C++20)
- Compile-time programming
- constexpr if (C++17)

### 27. Advanced Templates
- Template template parameters
- Fold expressions (C++17)
- CRTP (Curiously Recurring Template Pattern)
- Expression templates
- Policy-based design

## üöÄ Level 6: Expert Topics

### 28. Memory Management
- Stack vs heap
- Memory alignment
- Custom allocators
- Memory pools
- Cache-friendly code
- Memory order and barriers

### 29. Design Patterns
- Creational patterns (Singleton, Factory, Builder)
- Structural patterns (Adapter, Decorator, Proxy)
- Behavioral patterns (Observer, Strategy, Command)
- SOLID principles

### 30. Performance Optimization
- Profiling and benchmarking
- Cache optimization
- Inline assembly
- Compiler optimizations
- Branch prediction
- Loop unrolling
- SIMD operations

### 31. Low-Level Programming
- Bit manipulation techniques
- Endianness
- Memory-mapped I/O
- System calls
- Linking and loading
- Symbol tables

### 32. Advanced STL
- Custom comparators
- Custom allocators
- Iterator adaptors
- Ranges library (C++20)
- Views and projections

### 33. Concurrency Patterns
- Producer-consumer
- Reader-writer locks
- Lock-free programming
- Memory ordering
- Compare-and-swap operations

### 34. Modules (C++20)
- Module basics
- Module interfaces
- Import and export
- Module partitions

### 35. Coroutines (C++20)
- Coroutine basics
- co_await, co_yield, co_return
- Promise types
- Awaitable types
- Generator patterns

## üéØ Level 7: Specialized Topics

### 36. Generic Programming
- Concepts and constraints
- Variadic templates
- Type erasure
- Policy-based design

### 37. Network Programming
- Socket programming
- TCP/IP
- HTTP clients
- Asynchronous I/O

### 38. Graphics Programming
- OpenGL basics
- DirectX basics
- Vulkan basics
- Shader programming

### 39. Game Development
- Game loops
- Entity-component systems
- Physics engines
- Collision detection

### 40. Systems Programming
- Operating system interfaces
- Process and thread management
- Inter-process communication
- Device drivers basics

### 41. Embedded Systems
- Microcontroller programming
- Real-time systems
- Hardware interfaces
- Resource-constrained programming

### 42. Testing and Debugging
- Unit testing (Google Test, Catch2)
- Integration testing
- Debugging tools (GDB, Valgrind)
- Sanitizers (ASan, TSan, UBSan)
- Static analysis tools
- Code coverage

### 43. Build Systems
- Makefiles
- CMake
- Build configurations
- Cross-compilation
- Package managers (Conan, vcpkg)

### 44. Code Quality
- Code review practices
- Coding standards
- Documentation (Doxygen)
- Linting tools
- Continuous integration

---

## üìö Recommended Learning Path

### Phase 1 (1-2 months): Basics
Topics 1-10: Get comfortable with syntax and basic programming

### Phase 2 (2-3 months): OOP Mastery
Topics 11-15: Master object-oriented concepts

### Phase 3 (2-3 months): STL & Advanced Features
Topics 16-20: Learn templates and STL thoroughly

### Phase 4 (3-4 months): Modern C++
Topics 21-27: Embrace modern C++ features

### Phase 5 (Ongoing): Expert & Specialized
Topics 28-44: Pick areas based on your interests

